I am still fighting to gather all the details we need to ensure we adbide by the new laws and regulations. From what I have gathered so far we will need to change the games to a "Pre-Reveal" system.
What this means is the players must have the option to click a button to Reveal what they have won with-out the game playing, and/or for the amount to show right when the game starts.
Two places have already open their doors with updates they are trying, but yet do not know if they are within legal bounds.
Company A: They created two (2) Reveal buttons. One has the text "Reveal" and the other has "Reveal/Entertain". They also have a small black text box in the top left corner that shows the winning total when either button is clicked. When pressing the "Reveal" button the number changes in the top left to what they won and no game is played, and the money is added to their total winnings. When pressing the "Reveal/Entertain" button the total amount won is showed in the top left and then the game plays like normal.
Company B: This Company has made Three (3) buttons. First button is the normal "Reveal" button. After pressing this button it disappears and shows two other buttons in the same location, "Game", "No Game". When the "Reveal" button is pressed it shows the players total win in the message bar and shows the other two buttons. When the player presses "Game" it plays the game like normal, if they press "No Game". It adds the total to their winnings without a game play. The idea this company is going with is the players will double click the mouse over the "Reveal" button causing them to click "Reveal" and "Game" with out really noticing.
